// Figure 3.x: Data Consistency - Event-Driven Checkout Flow
// Sequence diagram showing cross-service data isolation

// ==================== ACTORS ====================
Client [icon: user, color: blue]
Basket API [icon: shopping-cart, color: green]
Redis [icon: redis, color: green]
Discount gRPC [icon: tag, color: orange]
RabbitMQ [icon: rabbitmq, color: yellow]
Ordering Consumer [icon: message-circle, color: purple]
Ordering API [icon: clipboard-list, color: purple]
SQL Server [icon: mssql, color: red]

// ==================== ADD TO CART (gRPC call) ====================
Client > Basket API : POST /Basket/CreateBasket
Basket API > Discount gRPC : GetDiscount(productName)
Discount gRPC > Basket API : CouponModel (amount)
Basket API > Redis : Save cart with discount applied
Basket API > Client : Cart response

// ==================== CHECKOUT (Event-driven) ====================
Client > Basket API : POST /Basket/Checkout
Basket API > Redis : GetBasketByUserNameQuery
Basket API > RabbitMQ : Publish BasketCheckoutEvent
Basket API > Redis : DeleteBasketByUserNameCommand
Basket API > Client : 202 Accepted

// ==================== ASYNC ORDER CREATION ====================
RabbitMQ > Ordering Consumer : Consume event
Ordering Consumer > Ordering API : CheckoutOrderCommand
Ordering API > SQL Server : INSERT Order
Ordering API > Ordering Consumer : Order created
Ordering Consumer > RabbitMQ : Acknowledge

// Key: Each service owns its database
// No cross-database transactions
// Eventual consistency via events
